      <hedline>
        <hl1>Death-Row Lawyer</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>M Michele Fournet letter says legal work by John Holdridge exonerated Louisiana death-row inmates Michael Ray Graham Jr and Albert Ronnie Burrell</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Two Death-Row Inmates Exonerated in Louisiana'' (news article, Jan. 6):</p>
        <p>Brilliant legal work in the companion cases of Michael Ray Graham Jr. and Albert Ronnie Burrell by John Holdridge, a New York University Law School graduate, is primarily responsible for the release of both inmates.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Two Death-Row Inmates Exonerated in Louisiana'' (news article, Jan. 6):</p>
        <p>Brilliant legal work in the companion cases of Michael Ray Graham Jr. and Albert Ronnie Burrell by John Holdridge, a New York University Law School graduate, is primarily responsible for the release of both inmates.</p>
        <p>Mr. Holdridge, whom I assisted in representing Mr. Graham, left a promising career with a Wall Street law firm to come to Louisiana to work as a capital defense lawyer.</p>
        <p>Few Americans know that some of the best legal minds in the country are, like Mr. Holdridge, doing this work exclusively and for only a subsistence income. They are the unsung heroes in the fight against the death penalty, the most outrageous human rights violation in the civilized world.</p>
        <p>M. MICHELE FOURNET  Baton Rouge, La., Jan. 8, 2001</p>
      </block>
